 President Trump's daughter Ivanka and her husband Jared Kushner at a reception in Jerusalem to mark the opening of the US embassy in the city. Photo: Getty AFP/Getty Images / The transfer has angered Palestinian leaders, who claim East Jerusalem as the capital of a future state. Ahead of the ceremony, a military spokesman said air strikes had destroyed a 1km tunnel built by the militant group Hamas and which had been tracked for weeks before being destroyed just inside the Gaza fence. "Hamas is spreading messages of its desire for a long-term ceasefire but actually digs terror tunnels into the territory of the state of Israel," said Avigdor Liberman, the Israeli defence minister. "We're not buying this bluff. 
